<h2 id="key-features">⚙️ Key Features for Tour Operators</h2>

<h3>Kiosk Mode with Offline Capability</h3>

Deploy iPads or Android tablets at your check-in points without worrying about connectivity. Waivers signed offline sync automatically when connection returns. For operations with remote launch points—river put-ins, trailheads, harbor docks—this feature alone justifies the subscription cost.

The kiosk mode also includes auto-reset functionality, so one guest's completed waiver clears before the next participant approaches. We've seen operations reduce check-in time by 70% using strategically placed kiosks versus the old paper-and-clipboard approach.

<h3>Minor Participant Handling</h3>

Tour operators serving families need waiver tools that properly capture guardian consent for participants under 18. Smartwaiver allows a single guardian to sign for multiple minors on one waiver, captures the legal relationship, and stores everything in a format that holds up in court.

The platform automatically flags when a minor attempts to sign without guardian consent and provides clear workflows for the common scenarios: parent signing for children, grandparent with legal guardianship, school group with teacher authorization forms.

<h3>Booking Platform Integrations</h3>

Native integrations with FareHarbor, Peek, Xola, Checkfront, and Rezdy mean waivers can be sent automatically at booking, with completion status visible in your reservation system. For operations processing hundreds of bookings weekly, this automation eliminates the manual tracking that previously required dedicated staff time.

<div class="callout-blue">
<strong>Pro Tip:</strong> Configure waiver reminder emails to send 48 hours before the tour, then again 24 hours before for unsigned waivers. Our data shows this timing achieves 85%+ pre-arrival signing rates, dramatically speeding up day-of check-in.
</div>

<h3>Photo and Video Consent Capture</h3>

Modern tour operators use guest photos and videos for marketing—but consent requirements have tightened significantly. Smartwaiver allows you to add media release sections to your liability waiver, capturing explicit consent for photo/video use across specific channels (social media, website, advertising).

This dual-purpose waiver approach means guests sign once for both liability and media consent, simplifying your legal compliance without adding friction to the check-in process.

<h3>Search and Retrieval</h3>

When an incident occurs—or worse, when attorneys contact you months later—finding the specific waiver fast is critical. Smartwaiver's search handles name, email, date range, and custom field queries. For operations processing 10,000+ waivers annually, the searchable database has proven invaluable during insurance claims and legal discovery.

We've worked with operators who kept seven years of paper waivers in storage units, paying hundreds monthly just to maintain access to documents they might never need. Digital storage with instant retrieval eliminates this cost entirely.

